25|$|The Rabbis {{taught that}} Rahab {{was one of}} the four most {{beautiful}} women who ever lived, along with Sarah, Abigail, and Esther. The Rabbis taught that Rahab inspired lust by <b>the</b> <b>mere</b> <b>mention</b> of her name. Rabbi Isaac taught that saying Rahab's name twice would cause a man immediately to lose control. Rav Nachman protested that he said Rahab's name twice and nothing happened to him. Rabbi Isaac replied that he meant that this would happen to any man who knew her.|$|E
